Click box to close.      
Full Title: Theory of Western Art Music: Harmonic Practices and Analysis I
Description: Textural deployments of harmony, tonic and dominant on the small and large scale, contrapuntal influences, cadential progressions, non-chord tones.
PreRequisite: Placement exam. A grade of at least C- is required in each course of the Music 5 series. Must be taken concurrently with the Music 4 series.
College: L&S
Units: 4.0
Grading: Letter
